                Erasmus students have the opportunity to study abroad in a wide range of destinations across Europe and beyond. These destinations include:
            </h1>
            <p>
                <strong>European Union Countries:</strong> Erasmus primarily focuses on study exchanges within European Union (EU) member states. This includes countries such as France, Germany, Spain, Italy, the United Kingdom, and many others.
                <br><br>
                <strong>Non-EU Countries:</strong> In addition to EU member states, Erasmus also offers study opportunities in non-EU countries that participate in the program. These countries may include Iceland, Norway, Liechtenstein, Turkey, North Macedonia, and Serbia, among others.
                <br><br>
                <strong>Partner Universities:</strong> Erasmus students can choose from a network of partner universities within their host country. These partner universities have established agreements with the student's home institution, allowing for seamless credit transfer and academic recognition.
                <br><br>
                <strong>Travel Opportunities:</strong> Studying abroad with Erasmus opens doors to travel opportunities within the host country and neighboring regions. Students can explore historic landmarks, natural wonders, and cultural attractions, creating unforgettable memories during their time abroad.
            </p>
